column20:
 Gold;
If you don't find a match in a certain amount of time you can enable an option that allows you to play against AI;
Game has enough different mechanics to standout from the crowd;
Cards seems balanced;
You can mix cards from different Aspects into your deck;
Simple and easy to use deck building tool with all the filters you'll probably need right now;
Cons:
The tutorial is lacking and does not explain the game mechanics very well

column21:
 if you are a total newbie to card games you will probably get confused;
There aren't many cards yet;
Some starter decks are way more useful than others (unmodified);
In short:
Fair business model

reviewText:
Pros:
- Free;
- Nice design of the cards and the game itself;
- Stable servers (at least for me);
- Good AI;
- You can have all the cards using just the money that you achieve in the game (more difficult and slow than using payed coins"
